 11  /-!
 12  # Isometries
 13  
 14  We define isometries, i.e., maps between emetric spaces that preserve
 15  the edistance (on metric spaces, these are exactly the maps that preserve distances),
 16  and prove their basic properties. We also introduce isometric bijections.
 17  -/
 18  
 19  noncomputable theory
 20  
 21  universes u v w
 22  variables {α : Type u} {β : Type v} {γ : Type w}
 23  
 24  open function set

 26  /-- An isometry (also known as isometric embedding) is a map preserving the edistance
 27  between emetric spaces, or equivalently the distance between metric space.  -/
 28  def isometry [emetric_space α] [emetric_space β] (f : α → β) : Prop :=
